&lt;p&gt;Clerical Officer/Receptionist&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Balderton Primary Care Centre Centre / Newark Health Centre&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;22.5 hours per week. Monday to Wednesday 8.30am to 5.00pm&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an enthusiastic individual to undertake the role of Clerical Officer/Receptionist within our health centre. As a member of the administration team you will ensure a high quality reception and efficient administration service is provided to staff and patients. You will be required to have good written and verbal communication skills as the role entails liaising with staff, GP Practices, clients and other agencies at all levels.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You should have previous clerical and computer experience, good keyboard skills and be educated to GCSE or equivalent level, with NVQ Level 2 in Business Administration. You should be able to work on your own initiative and be flexible to work within Health Centres across the region covered by Local Partnerships.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
